<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0222 </DOCNO><TEXT>From August 1977 through December 1983, sixty-one previously untreatedpatients with carcinoma of the hypopharynx were treated with radiationtherapy (RT) and surgery or RT alone. The level of cervical nodal involvementby UICC (1978) was more useful prognostic factor for the patients withnodal metastasis than N stage of TNM classification. Favorable nodalcontrol for N (+) cases was obtained by the combination of neck nodedissection and RT of more than 50 Gy. For N0 cases, more than 50 Gy ofelective RT which encompassed adequated field was necessary.</TEXT></DOC>